Node.Notes: The "pride of Jacob" is parallel to "our inheritance," and most likely refers to the land God gave Israel as an inheritance.
May refer to Jacob the patriarch himself or to the people of Israel.
Uncertain, Could be "as the people of the God of Abraham" or "with the people of the God of Abraham" (many believe that "with" was accidentally omitted).
Uncertain. Metaphor for protection (so protectors of the earth)? Some think a figurative extension to rulers (others change the text to read rulers). LXX has "mighty ones."
